# Force CRLF on checkout for Windows batch files. Without this, the
# line endings depend on each user's local core.autocrlf setting:
# autocrlf=true gives CRLF (works), but autocrlf=input or =false leaves
# LF on checkout, which breaks cmd.exe — the parser mis-tokenizes lines
# at LF boundaries (e.g. 'errorlevel' becomes 'rlevel', 'git rev-parse'
# becomes 'parse') because cmd expects CR+LF as the line terminator.
*.cmd text eol=crlf
*.bat text eol=crlf
